Iranian embassy siege remembered Thirty years on, former SAS man Pete Winner recalls the dramatic events which brought the Iranian embassy siege in London to an end. Pete was one of the SAS soldiers who stormed the building and he tells Matthew Bannister how he and his team helped to free hostages who had been held captive for six days. Sexual revolution in Chile For Outlook Alfonso Daniels has been to Santiago in Chile to find out why the country is apparently undergoing a sexual revolution. Show less